The following table was created as response to the SQL query
SELECT sbs_sbsname "SBS name", sbs_sbsnumber "SBS number", m_methodname "general method", ls_singlevalue "single value [mm^2]", ls_n "sample size", ls_valid "valid", ref_refname "reference", ls_mean "mean LS [mm^2]", ls_maximum "maximum LS [mm^2]", ls_minimum "minimum LS [mm^2]", ls_median "median LS [mm^2]", ls_replicates "number of replicates", ls_stddev "standard deviation", ls_stderror "standard error", ls_collectiondate "collection date", ls_comment "general comment", lflv_name "leaf state", or_origrefname "original reference" FROM (SELECT case when ls_median is not null then ls_median when ls_mean is not null then ls_mean when ls_minimum is not null and ls_maximum is not null then (ls_minimum + ls_maximum) / 2 when ls_minimum is not null then ls_minimum when ls_maximum is not null then ls_maximum else null end AS ls_singlevalue, sbs_sbsnumber, sbs_sbsname, m_methodname, ls_median, ls_mean, ls_minimum, ls_maximum, ls_n, ls_valid, ref_refname, ls_replicates, ls_stddev, ls_stderror, ls_collectiondate, ls_comment, lflv_name, or_origrefname, ls_sbsnumber FROM (SELECT sbs.sbs_sbsnumber, sbs.sbs_sbsname, m_ls.m_methodname, m_ls.ls_median, m_ls.ls_mean, m_ls.ls_minimum, m_ls.ls_maximum, m_ls.ls_n, m_ls.ls_valid, m_ls.ref_refname, m_ls.ls_replicates, m_ls.ls_stddev, m_ls.ls_stderror, m_ls.ls_collectiondate, m_ls.ls_comment, m_ls.lflv_name, m_ls.or_origrefname, m_ls.ls_sbsnumber FROM (SELECT speciesno AS sbs_sbsnumber, fullname AS sbs_sbsname FROM (SELECT fullname, speciesno, familyname, isinledalist from (select fullname, speciesno, family as familyid, isinledalist from taxon where specieslist = 60028) natural join taxonomicfamily)) sbs JOIN (SELECT r_ls.ls_sbsnumber, m.m_methodname, r_ls.ls_median, r_ls.ls_mean, r_ls.ls_minimum, r_ls.ls_maximum, r_ls.ls_n, r_ls.ls_valid, r_ls.ref_refname, r_ls.ls_replicates, r_ls.ls_stddev, r_ls.ls_stderror, r_ls.ls_collectiondate, r_ls.ls_comment, r_ls.lflv_name, r_ls.or_origrefname FROM (SELECT methodid AS m_methodid, methodname AS m_methodname FROM (select * from method_lv)) m JOIN (SELECT ls_lflv.ls_sbsnumber, ls_lflv.ls_methodid, ls_lflv.ls_median, ls_lflv.ls_mean, ls_lflv.ls_minimum, ls_lflv.ls_maximum, ls_lflv.ls_n, ls_lflv.ls_valid, r.ref_refname, ls_lflv.ls_replicates, ls_lflv.ls_stddev, ls_lflv.ls_stderror, ls_lflv.ls_collectiondate, ls_lflv.ls_comment, ls_lflv.lflv_name, ls_lflv.or_origrefname FROM (SELECT referenceid AS ref_referenceid, refname AS ref_refname FROM (select referenceid, refname, reftypeid from reference)) r LEFT JOIN (SELECT ls_orf.ls_sbsnumber, ls_orf.ls_methodid, ls_orf.ls_median, ls_orf.ls_mean, ls_orf.ls_minimum, ls_orf.ls_maximum, ls_orf.ls_n, ls_orf.ls_valid, ls_orf.ls_referenceid, ls_orf.ls_replicates, ls_orf.ls_stddev, ls_orf.ls_stderror, ls_orf.ls_collectiondate, ls_orf.ls_comment, lflv.lflv_name, ls_orf.or_origrefname FROM (SELECT ls.ls_sbsnumber, ls.ls_methodid, ls.ls_median, ls.ls_mean, ls.ls_minimum, ls.ls_maximum, ls.ls_n, ls.ls_valid, ls.ls_referenceid, ls.ls_replicates, ls.ls_stddev, ls.ls_stderror, ls.ls_collectiondate, ls.ls_comment, ls.ls_leafformid, orf.or_origrefname FROM (SELECT sbsnumber AS ls_sbsnumber, methodid AS ls_methodid, median AS ls_median, mean AS ls_mean, minimum AS ls_minimum, maximum AS ls_maximum, n AS ls_n, valid AS ls_valid, referenceid AS ls_referenceid, replicates AS ls_replicates, stddeviation AS ls_stddev, stderror AS ls_stderror, collectiondate AS ls_collectiondate, p_comment AS ls_comment, leafformid AS ls_leafformid, origreferenceid AS ls_origreferenceid FROM (SELECT sbsnumber, taxonid, mean, median, minimum, maximum, stderror, stddeviation, n, replicates, created_when, updated_when, collectiondate, p_comment, methodid, referenceid, origreferenceid, habitattypeid, georefid, valid, validsince, validuntil, ledaid, batchid, leafformid, leafsizeid FROM leafsize natural join taxontosbsassignment WHERE valid IN (-2, 1))) ls FULL JOIN (SELECT origreferenceid AS or_origrefid, origrefname AS or_origrefname FROM (select referenceid as origreferenceid, refname as origrefname, reftypeid as origreftypeid from reference)) orf ON ls.ls_origreferenceid = orf.or_origrefid) ls_orf FULL JOIN (SELECT leafformid AS lflv_id, leafformname AS lflv_name FROM (select leafformid, leafformname from leafform_lv)) lflv ON ls_orf.ls_leafformid = lflv.lflv_id) ls_lflv ON r.ref_referenceid = ls_lflv.ls_referenceid) r_ls ON m.m_methodid = r_ls.ls_methodid) m_ls ON sbs.sbs_sbsnumber = m_ls.ls_sbsnumber)) ORDER BY sbs_sbsname
